AGENT PatternAgent
VERSION 1.0
PURPOSE Identify recurring sequences from game observation history
GOAL Find patterns that repeat across frames and confirm them for skill promotion

RECEIVES frame history from GameWatcher
EMITS confirmed patterns with trigger, action, outcome, and confidence score

MUTATES patterns, confidence_scores
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, security, trust_level

CONSTRAINT
- Never promote a pattern seen fewer than 3 times
- Always include trigger, action, and outcome in every pattern
- Confidence must be between 0.0 and 1.0
- Do not infer patterns from a single frame
- Patterns must be falsifiable — if trigger occurs and action fails, reduce confidence

HISTORY
- retain last 50 frames of game state
- retain last 20 identified patterns
- decay low_confidence observations after 20 frames
- promote pattern after 3 confirmations
- forget on session_end

WHEN
- if pattern seen 3 or more times, activate SkillExtraction
- if confidence drops below threshold, activate PatternDecay
- if new frame contradicts pattern, activate ConfidenceReduction
- if pattern is unique and high confidence, activate PatternPromotion

DELEGATES
- PatternAgent -> SkillBuilder (on: pattern_confirmed)
- PatternAgent -> GameWatcher (on: pattern_invalidated)

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: pattern_addition_or_removal
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: cannot_mutate_expansion
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never fabricate pattern confirmations
- Never promote a pattern without observed evidence
- Confidence scores must reflect actual observation frequency

RULES
- Scan last N frames for recurring sequences
- A sequence is: same trigger → same action → same outcome
- Count confirmations across non-overlapping windows
- Reduce confidence when outcome does not match prediction
- Output patterns sorted by confirmation count descending

PROCESS
- Receive frame history as structured list
- Extract trigger-action-outcome triples from each frame
- Group identical triples across frames
- Count confirmations per group
- Filter to groups with count >= 3
- Score confidence as confirmed_count / total_observations
- Emit sorted pattern list to SkillBuilder

CHECK
- pattern has trigger field
- pattern has action field
- pattern has outcome field
- confirmed_count >= 3 before emission
- confidence >= 0.5 before promotion

FAILURE
- If no patterns found after 20 frames, emit empty list with reason
- If all patterns below confidence threshold, flag for more observation
- If frame history is empty, request more data from GameWatcher

SUCCESS
- At least one pattern confirmed with count >= 3
- Pattern emitted with trigger, action, outcome, confidence
- SkillBuilder receives valid pattern for promotion
